<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,152,504]" pageId="6" pageNumber="375">
Comments: 
<taxonomicName authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[337,617,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Systellapha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatithorax">
<emphasis box="[337,617,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="375">Systellapha ornatithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from congeners in details of the genital fork, phallic bulb, spermathecal ducts and pigmentation, but similarities such as the elongate male terminalia, the four similarly shaped spermathecae, and the dark thorax with silvery microtrichose areas reflect a close relationship. Enderlein indicated that he thought this species was closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Enderlein" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[709,1023,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Systellapha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis box="[709,904,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="375">Systellapha varia</emphasis>
Enderlein
</taxonomicName>
, however 
<taxonomicName authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[1136,1223,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Systellapha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis box="[1136,1223,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="375">S. varia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
